Like a (dark) phoenix rising from the ashes, we are BACK to cover part 2 of our 2-part review of Grant Morrison's new X-Men. In this latter half of the story, we tackle the Weapon's Plus Program, a whodunit murder mystery at Xavier's mansion, and a dark reveal of who has been pulling our heroes' strings the entire time. Plus we discuss Morrison's constant battle with editorial, his rejected pitches, and his role in X-Men history in this deep dive into issues 139-154!

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

